 Postscript. Explanation of the colors attached to the letters.
 - Blue is the image of a mountain top. Enlightenment, wisdom, excellence. Prajnaparamita, anuttara samyak sambodhi, ultimate nirvana.
 - Yellow is a word referring to a person. Kanjizajibodhisattva = Bodhisattva&#22517;, Sharishi = Saariputta, the Buddhas of the three generations.
 - Light blue is the word for empty, nothingness, and the "remove" system. I think some may object to the idea of grouping removing with empty or nothing.
 - Red is the thing. The part of "~" referred to as "~ is empty" or "~ does not exist." All things and senses = the five skandhas, color, thought, action, perception, eye, ear, nose, tongue, body and will, color, voice, smell, taste, touch, etc. It is a little regrettable that the three-fold meta-reference of "no more ignorance and no more exhaustion of ignorance" is not fully expressed in colors.
 - Purple is a spell. 
